$\sqrt{s_{\rm NN}}$ = 200 GeV for identified particles as well as their antiparticles. The Tsallis form of invariant yield including $\mu$ is used in Fig. ~\ref{fig9}. It fits up to $p_{\rm T}$ $\sim$ 3 GeV for both most central and most peripheral collisions. The goodness of fit can be seen from $\chi^{2}$/ndf  values shown in Figs. ~\ref{fig10} and ~\ref{fig11}. 

