The fitting is performed up to $p_{\rm T}$ $\sim$ 3 GeV in A+A collisions and $p_{\rm T}$ $\sim$ 2.5 GeV in $p+p$ collisions, only a slight deviation at higher $p_{\rm T}$ is observed in pion spectra. The values of various parameters obtained from the fits are provided in Table.~\ref{table3}. It is observed from the values of $\chi^{2} /ndf$ (Table.~\ref{table3}) that the performance of the present approach is quite satisfactory, except in case of pion, which can be seen from the Figs.~\ref{fig18} and~\ref{fig19}.

